<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-849-260  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 849 260.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>InfoWorld  Nov 6 1989 v11 n45 p63(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>A short guide to the font wars.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Seybold, Jonathon.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Apple and Microsoft Corp have signed an agreement under whichMicrosoft will integrate Apple's Royal outline font technologyinto OS/2 Presentation Manager and the MS-DOS-based MicrosoftWindows.andP;  Apple and Microsoft will develop an open font standardso third parties can make and market fonts that will run on themany machines affected by the agreement.andP;  Adobe has responded bypublishing its Postscript language specification, including theformat for Type One fonts, and proceeding with its Adobe TypeManager font technology for both PCs and Macintoshes.andP;  Adobe willalso extend Postscript aggressively.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Microsoft Corp. (contracts)Apple Computer Inc. (contracts)Adobe Systems Inc. (planning).andO;Topic:     FontsPage Description LanguagesCompetitionContractsLicensingStrategic Planning.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>